    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="745"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.68/71</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-10">October 10,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Greek Minister called to see me. The Minister stated that now that the King
                    of the Hellenes and the Greek Government were established <pb facs="0764"
                        n="752" xml:id="pg_752"/> in London, he hoped that a new American Minister
                    would be appointed near that Government to replace Mr. MacVeagh.</p>
                <p>I said I would be very happy to take this matter up with the President and that I
                    felt sure that the President would desire Mr. Biddle to be accredited to the
                    Greek Government. I said that as soon as I received the President’s approval I
                    would request the <hi rend="italic">agrément</hi> for Mr. Biddle through the
                        Minister.<note n="33" xml:id="d745fn33">President Roosevelt gave his
                        approval, October 14, 1941, and Anthony J. Drexel Biddle, Jr., was appointed
                        Minister to Greece, November 13, 1941.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
